### 3. C++ Algorithm Engine Design

Each data structure maps to a specific feature. The engine communicates with Node.js via **stdin/stdout JSON protocol** (the Node.js backend spawns the C++ binary as a child process and exchanges JSON messages).

| Data Structure | Feature | Time Complexity | Space Complexity | Why Used |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Trie** | Autocomplete & prefix search | O(L) insert/search, O(L + N) autocomplete | O(ALPHABET √ó L √ó N) | Fastest prefix matching ‚Äî type "Jo" and instantly get "John", "Joseph", "Jordan" |
| **HashMap** | Duplicate detection | O(1) avg lookup | O(N) | Hash phone/email ‚Üí detect duplicates in O(1) before insert |
| **Merge Sort** | Alphabetical sort | O(N log N) guaranteed | O(N) | Stable sort ‚Äî preserves order of equal elements (important for contacts with same last name) |
| **Quick Sort** | Sort by date/count | O(N log N) average | O(log N) | In-place sort, fast average case for numeric fields |
| **Binary Search** | Search in sorted data | O(log N) | O(1) | After sorting, find contacts by name in O(log N) |
| **Priority Queue** | Recently contacted | O(log N) insert/extract | O(N) | Max-heap by `lastContacted` ‚Äî always shows most recent at top |
| **Stack (LIFO)** | Undo delete | O(1) push/pop | O(N) | Last deleted contact is first to restore ‚Äî natural undo behavior |
| **Queue (FIFO)** | Search history | O(1) enqueue/dequeue | O(K) fixed size | Maintains last K searches in order ‚Äî oldest auto-evicted |
| **BST** | Alphabetical storage & range queries | O(log N) avg | O(N) | Ordered traversal gives sorted contacts; range queries like "all contacts A-M" |
| **Graph** | Relationship suggestions (optional) | O(V + E) BFS/DFS | O(V + E) | Contacts sharing company/city form edges ‚Äî suggest "people you may know" |

**Communication Protocol**: Node.js sends JSON commands to the C++ binary's stdin, and reads JSON responses from stdout. Example:

```json
// Request
{"action": "trie_search", "prefix": "Jo", "contacts": [...]}

// Response  
{"status": "ok", "results": ["John Doe", "Joseph Smith"], "time_ms": 0.3}
```

